<P>THE Young Mans claim unto the Sacrament OF THE LORDS-SUPPER.</P>
<P>OR The EXAMINATION of a Per&s;on approaching to the Table of the LORD.</P>
<P>Compos'd By the Reverend Mr. JOHN QUICK, Mini&s;ter of the Go&s;pel, in <HI>London.</HI></P>
<P>And now, in a <HI>Second Impre&s;&s;ion,</HI> Offer'd unto the Churches of <HI>New England</HI>; by Sundry Mini&s;ters of tho&s;e Churches, Approving of it, and Atte&s;ting to it.</P>
<P>With a Defence of <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Churches, from what is Offen&s;ive to them, in a Di&s;+cour&s;e lately Publi&s;hed, under the Title of, <HI>The Doctrine of In|&s;tituted Churches.</HI></P>
<P>By certain Ministers of the Go&s;pel, in <HI>Bo&s;ton.</HI></P>
<P><HI>BOSTON,</HI> Printed by <HI>B Green,</HI> and <HI>J Allen,</HI> for <HI>Samuel Phillips,</HI> at the Brick Shop near the Old Meeting Hou&s;e 1700.</P>
