<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word">, That the <HI>Twelve Hundred and Sixty years</HI> are too near out, for him to Expect it Our Friend abhors, we know, &s;uch an I&s;&s;ue of his <HI>Hypothe&s;is</HI>: but we do not know, how it will be Staved off, or how an <HI>Oecumenical</HI> Church is le&s;s of a <HI>Divine Right,</HI> than a <HI>National</HI>: or at lea&s;t, a Church of <HI>Europe</HI> than a Church of <HI>England.</HI> The more Sober Divines in the Church of <HI>England,</HI> which are for a <HI>National Church,</HI> but not for a <HI>Foreign Ju|ri&s;diction,</HI> would yet have it Recognized as being of no more than an <HI>Humane Right</HI>; nor do they &s;ee, how without the hazard of <HI>High Trea&s;on,</HI> and of a <HI>Foreign Juri&s;diction</HI> <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o have it otherwi&s;e&punc; and among others the Ingenuous Author of, <HI>Catholici&s;m wi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">hout Popery,</HI> giving us the <HI>Scheme,</HI> which the late <HI>Queen,</HI> and <HI>Arch<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">bi&s;hop,</HI> would have Pro&s;ecuted, if <HI>Death</HI> had not cut off their Noble Purpo|&s;es, does confe&s;s,
